                                   <p id="CA.DIR.USAC.23.171020051449.2221">The Canada Mortgage and Housing Corpn was established as a federal crown corporation in 1946 to administer the National Housing Act. It administers numerous federal housing programmes, including a scheme of providing loans to first-time home buyers, the construction of `affordable’ housing, and the renovation of some areas of social housing.</p>
